<br>
She walked out on the large balcony, overlooking Greece....A smile on her lips as the wind picked up, she closed her eyes and her brown hair waved in the breeze. She took a deep breath and spoke:<br>
<br>
&quot;Tis the season of change, kiss goodbye to the warmth.&quot;<br>
<br>
She blew a kiss off the balcony. The trees were allready bare and the flowers asleep, awaiting next spring when they would wake up too show off there radient colors once again.<br>
<br>
She raised her arms in the air, the sky slowly covering with cloud cover. A few flurries began to fall to the ground....<br>
The first snowfall of the season began, soon the lands of Greece would be blanketed in the white magestic snow.<br>
<br>
She leaned on the balcony and watched the snow fall  <p>:*: Goddess Demeter, Goddess of the Harvest. Controller of the seasons and weather. :*:  )O(</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=vasilissadelerium>Vasilissa De Lerium</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Vasilissa Apo Themiscrya</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#993300>(12/21/02 6:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=418.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/deleriuml9/images/del2.bmp WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Seasons</span><hr size=1> She was outside gathering wood for the fire when the first snowflakes began to fall. She looked up and smiled.<br>
<br>
&quot; Demeter be blessed.&quot;<br>
<br>
De' Lerium walked into the shed and grabbed a wheelbarrel. Bringing it outside, she put the cut pieces of wood into it. She then headed out a bit to the stockpile and threw more into it. Once greatly filled, she walked the wheelbarrel to the Labrys and emptied it on the side of the building.<br>
<br>
Turning, she went back to the stockpile and filled up again, then headed to her hut and wheeled it to the front. She grabbed as much as she could hold and brought it into her hut. In and out she walked until the barrel was empty. Having been stocked up, she started a fire in her fire place. <br>
<br>
